It's time to renovate the bedroom thoroughly. It's the last room in the house that only has simple decorations.
Remove the ugly electric fireplace and hearth. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint it. Install a custom closet.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch....
The chaotic phase is over.
Several dead birds, whose bodies were completely dried out, were found behind the chimney :(.
Prepare to meet the plasterers for next week.
Satisfied with the small recess next to it.
Put the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing yet 😈)
Ha ha, take a look at what we found behind the radiator!
Do you remember adding those cute little ventilation openings to prevent the chimney from getting damp?
Sweep installed both the chimney cap and the chimney cover. These should make it safer for the crows that like to nest in the chimney. 🪖
The plasterer is done. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork mat has already been installed, and toilet paper rolls have been used as accessories for the vacuum cleaner to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has already been prepared, and we can start laying it now. Let's have a cup of tea and rest for a while.
Okay, today's progress is a bit slow because we need to cut around the doorframes to ensure a seamless connection with the corridor (which is also being flooring), which is quite challenging to operate. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me.
Phew, it's finally finished, but everything is in such a mess! To top it off, the assembly instructions for the new bed were terrible. I can finally have a good night's sleep tonight!
There are still the corridor floor and baseboards left to do. The decorators won't come until a month later, so we can only make do for now, with just bare plasterboard in the rooms.
Simplify the process a bit in the evening by cutting off a portion of the bottom of the doorframe with a tenon saw and chisels, so that the floor can fit perfectly underneath.
The softwood flooring in the corridor has also been installed.
Yesterday, we also laid the floor in the corridor! This morning, we got up at 5 o'clock to go to Heathrow Airport to retrieve Package No. 1, and then took a nap. Now, we can finally start installing the baseboard in the corridor. We'll fill any gaps after the glue dries.
